The transmissible spongiform encephalopathies (TSEs or prion diseases) form a group of fatal neurodegenerative diseases including bovine spongiform encephalopathy, Creutzfeldt to Jakob disease (CJD) and Gerstmann to Straussler to Scheinker syndrome (GSS). These diseases are characterized by the accumulation in the brain of abnormal protease-resistant isoforms of prion protein (PrP), termed PrPSc
